# ScrapCo V2 — Mobile Requirements (Expo)

## 1. Mobile Philosophy

The mobile app is:

- Operational interface for sellers and vendors
- Real-time interaction layer
- Push-notification enabled client
- Location-aware system
- Lightweight, performant, and scalable

Mobile is NOT:

- SEO surface
- Marketing site
- Business logic authority

All business logic remains server-side.

---

## 2. Platform Targets

Supported platforms:

- Android (Primary)
- iOS
- Web (optional minimal support)

Android must be prioritized for early cities.

---

## 3. Core Roles

Mobile must support:

- SELLER
- VENDOR

ADMIN must remain web-only in Phase 1.

---

## 4. Core Seller Flows

Seller must be able to:

1. Register/Login
2. Create pickup request
3. View pickup status in real-time
4. Receive push notifications
5. View transaction history
6. Submit rating
7. Cancel pickup (before completion)

No polling allowed.

---

## 5. Core Vendor Flows

Vendor must be able to:

1. Login
2. Receive offer notification
3. Accept / Reject offer
4. View assigned pickups
5. Mark pickup ON_THE_WAY
6. Mark pickup COMPLETED
7. View earnings summary (Phase 2)
8. Update availability status

Vendor must receive real-time updates.

---

## 6. Real-Time Integration

Mobile must use:

- Supabase Realtime OR
- WebSocket client

Polling via setInterval is prohibited.

Client must:

- Subscribe to user-scoped channels
- Reconcile state on reconnect
- Automatically reconnect if dropped

---

## 7. Push Notifications

Push must trigger on:

- New vendor offer
- Offer expiring soon
- Pickup assigned
- Pickup started
- Pickup completed
- Transaction settled

Push must:

- Use Expo Notifications
- Be token-registered securely
- Not contain sensitive data
- Deep link to relevant screen

---

## 8. Location Handling

Location must:

- Request permission only when needed
- Not request on app startup unnecessarily
- Not block UI if denied
- Support background updates for vendor (optional Phase 2)

Vendor location updates must:

- Be authenticated
- Not be publicly writable
- Be rate-limited

---

## 9. State Management

Use:

- Modular feature-based context
- React Query (optional for data caching)
- Minimal global providers

Avoid:

- Single global provider wrapping entire app
- Unnecessary re-render cascades
- Polling-based state updates

---

## 10. Security Requirements

Mobile must:

- Store tokens in SecureStore
- Never hardcode API keys
- Never hardcode Google Maps key
- Validate API base URL at startup
- Disable dev bypass in production build

Sensitive configuration must use:

```

EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL

```id="g1zbrm"

No fallback to localhost in production.

---

## 11. Performance Requirements

App must:

- Avoid heavy libraries unless required
- Lazy-load heavy screens
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders
- Debounce rapid state updates
- Avoid blocking UI thread

Target:

- Smooth performance on low-end Android devices

---

## 12. Navigation Architecture

Use:

- React Navigation
- Separate stacks per role
- Auth gate at root

Example structure:

```

navigation/
├── AuthStack
├── SellerStack
├── VendorStack

```id="u9fh0x"

Role-based routing required.

---

## 13. API Client Requirements

Mobile must use:

- Centralized API client
- Typed responses
- Standard error handling
- Automatic JWT injection
- Graceful retry logic

No raw fetch scattered across components.

---

## 14. Error Handling

Mobile must:

- Display meaningful errors
- Support retry
- Avoid crashing entire app
- Log errors to monitoring service
- Handle offline mode gracefully

---

## 15. Offline Strategy (Basic)

In Phase 1:

- Allow viewing last-known state
- Prevent critical actions offline
- Show offline banner

No complex offline queue required initially.

---

## 16. Accessibility

Mobile must:

- Use accessibilityLabel
- Support screen readers
- Support larger text
- Avoid animation overload
- Respect reduced motion

---

## 17. Build & Environment Rules

Production build must:

- Strip console logs
- Disable dev flags
- Validate environment variables
- Use correct API endpoint
- Use restricted Google Maps key (if used)

No debug configuration allowed in production.

---

## 18. Analytics

Mobile must support:

- Pickup creation event tracking
- Offer acceptance tracking
- Session tracking
- Error tracking

Analytics must not block UI thread.

---

## 19. Guardrails

Mobile must never:

- Poll for status
- Store sensitive secrets
- Allow admin role access
- Use env toggle auth
- Accept unsigned webhook
- Assume dispatch state locally

Mobile is a real-time client, not business authority.

---

## 20. Summary

ScrapCo Mobile must be:

- Real-time
- Push-enabled
- Secure
- Role-aware
- Location-capable
- Performant
- Offline-tolerant (basic)
- Scalable
- Cleanly structured

It is the operational interface of the marketplace.
